', '<p>The Asian Physics Olympiad (APhO), initiated in the year of 2000 by Indonesia, is an annual international physics competition devoted to secondary school students in Asia. It is usually held in late April or early May, and more than 20 countries participate in it regularly. It is very similar in style and process to <a href="/olympiads/ipho">IPhO</a>, except each participating country can send 8 contestants at most instead of 5 in IPhO. Hence, it is often used by countries as a selection test to decide who goes to IPhO.</p>
<p>Most of the files here are from <a href="https://stefanivanov.site/teaching/">Stefan Ivanov&#39;s</a> archive. Take note of the <a href="https://stefanivanov.site/teaching/errata.pdf">errata list</a>.</p>
', '{"problems":{"label":"Problems"},"problemsEn":{"label":"Problems (EN)"},"theory":{"label":"Theory"},"experiment":{"label":"Experiment"},"solutions":{"label":"Solutions"},"answerSheet":{"label":"Answer Sheets"},"theorySolutions":{"label":"Theory Solutions"},"experimentSolutions":{"label":"Experiment Solutions"},"theoryMarkingScheme":{"label":"Theory Marking Scheme"},"experimentMarkingScheme":{"label":"Experiment Marking Scheme"},"theoryInstructions":{"label":"Theory General Instructions"},"experimentalInstructions":{"label":"Experiment General Instructions"},"experimentalFiles":{"label":"Experimental Files"},"experimentalPresentation":{"label":"Experimental Presentation"},"report":{"label":"Report"},"results":{"label":"Results"},"minutes":{"label":"Minutes"},"proceedings":{"label":"Proceedings"},"comments":{"label":"Comments"}}', '{"problem":{"label":"Problem"},"problemEn":{"label":"Problem (EN)"},"solution":{"label":"Solution"},"answerSheet":{"label":"Answer Sheet"},"markingScheme":{"label":"Marking Scheme"},"presentation":{"label":"Presentation"},"alignmentChart":{"label":"Alignment Chart"},"handwrittenSolution":{"label":"Solution (Handwritten)"}}');
', '<p>The Nordic-Baltic Physics Olympiad (NBPhO) is a regional physics olympiad for students in Estonia, Finland, Sweden and Latvia. It serves as a selection test for the International Physics Olympiad (IPhO) and is held annually in the spring. The problems tend to be highly insightful, reminiscent of <a href="/olympiads/eupho">EuPhO</a>, but easier and more guided. Check out the <a href="https://nbpho.ee/">official website</a> and <a href="https://stefanivanov.site/teaching/errata.pdf">errata</a> for more information.</p>
', '{"problems":{"label":"Problems"},"problemsEn":{"label":"Problems (EN)"},"theory":{"label":"Theory"},"experiment":{"label":"Experiment"},"solutions":{"label":"Solutions"},"answerSheet":{"label":"Answer Sheets"},"theorySolutions":{"label":"Theory Solutions"},"experimentSolutions":{"label":"Experiment Solutions"},"theoryMarkingScheme":{"label":"Theory Marking Scheme"},"experimentMarkingScheme":{"label":"Experiment Marking Scheme"},"theoryInstructions":{"label":"Theory General Instructions"},"experimentalInstructions":{"label":"Experiment General Instructions"},"experimentalFiles":{"label":"Experimental Files"},"experimentalPresentation":{"label":"Experimental Presentation"},"report":{"label":"Report"},"results":{"label":"Results"},"minutes":{"label":"Minutes"},"proceedings":{"label":"Proceedings"},"comments":{"label":"Comments"}}', '{"problem":{"label":"Problem"},"problemEn":{"label":"Problem (EN)"},"solution":{"label":"Solution"},"answerSheet":{"label":"Answer Sheet"},"markingScheme":{"label":"Marking Scheme"},"presentation":{"label":"Presentation"}}');
', '<p>This is the second round of selection for the U.S. Physics Team. You are given 90 minutes for each part (A and B) of the competition, with a short break in between. For more information, see <a href="https://www.aapt.org/physicsteam/">the official website</a>.</p>
