', '<p>The International Zhautykov Olympiad (IZhO) is an annual multi-subject olympiad comprising of Mathematics, Physics and Computing. It is held in Kazakhstan and is named after the Kazakh mathematician and educator, Ilyas Zhautykov. The IZhO attracts top high school students from around the world to compete in challenging problems across these three subjects. The competition aims to foster international cooperation and promote excellence in science and mathematics among young students. </p>
<p>Unfortunately, the Physics problems in this olympiad have many mistakes, as detailed in the <a href="https://stefanivanov.site/teaching/errata.pdf">errata list</a>.</p>
', '{"problems":{"label":"Problems"},"problemsEn":{"label":"Problems (EN)"},"theory":{"label":"Theory"},"experiment":{"label":"Experiment"},"solutions":{"label":"Solutions"},"answerSheet":{"label":"Answer Sheets"},"theorySolutions":{"label":"Theory Solutions"},"experimentSolutions":{"label":"Experiment Solutions"},"theoryMarkingScheme":{"label":"Theory Marking Scheme"},"experimentMarkingScheme":{"label":"Experiment Marking Scheme"},"theoryInstructions":{"label":"Theory General Instructions"},"experimentalInstructions":{"label":"Experiment General Instructions"},"experimentalFiles":{"label":"Experimental Files"},"experimentalPresentation":{"label":"Experimental Presentation"},"report":{"label":"Report"},"results":{"label":"Results"},"minutes":{"label":"Minutes"},"proceedings":{"label":"Proceedings"},"comments":{"label":"Comments"}}', '{"problem":{"label":"Problem"},"problemEn":{"label":"Problem (EN)"},"solution":{"label":"Solution"},"answerSheet":{"label":"Answer Sheet"},"markingScheme":{"label":"Marking Scheme"},"presentation":{"label":"Presentation"}}');
