SJPO does have quite a few errors, unfortunately. I have started to maintain an [errata page](https://apochrome.notion.site/SJPO-Errata-315b933f14fe800994d1f9d524ab1f39?source=copy_link) here. I do not have time to go through every paper, so I would appreciate it if you dropp me an email when you find an error. See errata page for my email address.
', '<p>The Singapore Junior Physics Olympiad (SJPO) is an algebra-based olympiad for secondary school students that assumes no knowledge of calculus. It is quite well-set, with many thought-provoking problems. The time pressure can be quite high, with olympiadants having to solve 50 multiple-choice questions in 2 hours. The questions here are from the general round. In 2024 there was some technical issue which caused the competition to have to be taken again, so there are two versions of the problems. SJPO 2020 is pointless as it was a compilation of past year problems, so I won&#39;t include it here. There were some technical issues in 2021 so it didn&#39;t really work out. I&#39;ve tried my best to find as many papers as I can, but if you have a paper or its solutions that isn&#39;t here, do let me know. I thank the folks at <a href="https://www.pd-stem.com/">PD Stem Education</a> for making solutions to 2022 and 2024, found <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/18B5GEA6r5dmef2QbzQteKk3EKrXxuU05">here</a>.</p>
<p>SJPO does have quite a few errors, unfortunately. I have started to maintain an <a href="https://apochrome.notion.site/SJPO-Errata-315b933f14fe800994d1f9d524ab1f39?source=copy_link">errata page</a> here. I do not have time to go through every paper, so I would appreciate it if you dropp me an email when you find an error. See errata page for my email address.</p>
